It doesn't support Tensor Flow or Matlab out of the box, but it has the potential to become the coolest tool in town. The fastest way to make this more popular is to create a widget for raspberry pi and/or Arduino (i.e. with code easy to understand). The Arduino website can promote the tool for free. Orange could also compete with Minitab and other statistical packages, descriptive statistics, comparative statistics, Full Factorial experiments, etc. This tools has a lot of upside potential.
